# Database Schema Rules

## Database Overview

### Technology Stack
- **Prisma ORM** for database operations
- **SQLite** for development (file:./prisma/dev.db)
- **PostgreSQL** recommended for production
- **Migration-based** schema management

### Design Principles
- **Relational design** with proper relationships
- **Data integrity** through constraints
- **Performance optimization** with indexes
- **Scalability** considerations for multi-tenancy

## Core Models

### 1. User Model
```prisma
model User {
  id            String   @id @default(cuid())
  email         String   @unique
  name          String
  password      String
  role          UserRole
  isActive      Boolean  @default(true) // For account-level suspension control
  // One-to-one relationship with Organization
  organization  Organization? @relation(fields: [id], references: [adminId])
  createdAt     DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt     DateTime @updatedAt

  // One-to-one relationship with Admin User
  admin       User @relation(fields: [adminId], references: [id])
  // Relations
  sessions      Session[]
  tickets       Ticket[]
  audits        Audit[]

  @@index([email])
  @@index([role])
  // One-to-one relationship indexed by adminId
}
```

### 2. Organization Model
```prisma
model Organization {
  id          Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
  name        String
  description String?
  status      OrganizationStatus @default(PENDING)
  logo        String?
  website     String?
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt

  // One-to-one relationship with Admin User
  admin       User @relation(fields: [adminId], references: [id])
  // Relations
  users       User[]
  elections   Election[]
  tickets     Ticket[]

  @@index([status])
  @@index([name])
}
```

### 3. Election Model
```prisma
model Election {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  title       String
  description String?
  status      ElectionStatus @default(DRAFT)
  startDate   DateTime?
  endDate     DateTime?
  organizationId Int
  organization Organization @relation(fields: [organizationId], references: [id])
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt

  // One-to-one relationship with Admin User
  admin       User @relation(fields: [adminId], references: [id])
  // Relations
  votingScopes    VotingScope[]
  parties         Party[]
  positions       Position[]
  candidates      Candidate[]
  voters          Voter[]
  votes           Vote[]
  surveys         Survey[]
  tickets         Ticket[]

  // One-to-one relationship indexed by adminId
  @@index([status])
  @@index([startDate, endDate])
}
```

### 4. VotingScope Model
```prisma
model VotingScope {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  name        String
  description String?
  parentId    String?
  parent      VotingScope? @relation("ScopeHierarchy", fields: [parentId], references: [id])
  children    VotingScope[] @relation("ScopeHierarchy")
  electionId  String
  election    Election @relation(fields: [electionId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt

  // One-to-one relationship with Admin User
  admin       User @relation(fields: [adminId], references: [id])
  // Relations
  voters      Voter[]
  votes       Vote[]

  @@index([electionId])
  @@index([parentId])
}
```

### 5. Party Model
```prisma
model Party {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  name        String
  description String?
  logo        String?
  color       String?
  electionId  String
  election    Election @relation(fields: [electionId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt

  // One-to-one relationship with Admin User
  admin       User @relation(fields: [adminId], references: [id])
  // Relations
  candidates  Candidate[]

  @@index([electionId])
  @@unique([name, electionId])
}
```

### 6. Position Model
```prisma
model Position {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  title       String
  description String?
  requirements String?
  maxCandidates Int    @default(1)
  electionId  String
  election    Election @relation(fields: [electionId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt

  // One-to-one relationship with Admin User
  admin       User @relation(fields: [adminId], references: [id])
  // Relations
  candidates  Candidate[]

  @@index([electionId])
  @@unique([title, electionId])
}
```

### 7. Candidate Model
```prisma
model Candidate {
  id          String   @id @default(cuid())
  name        String
  bio         String?
  image       String?
  manifesto   String?
  positionId  String
  position    Position @relation(fields: [positionId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  partyId     String?
  party       Party? @relation(fields: [partyId], references: [id])
  electionId  String
  election    Election @relation(fields: [electionId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  updatedAt   DateTime @updatedAt

  // One-to-one relationship with Admin User
  admin       User @relation(fields: [adminId], references: [id])
