## Database Relationships

### One-to-Many Relationships
- **Organization → Users**: One organization can have many users
- **Organization → Elections**: One organization can have many elections
- **Election → VotingScopes**: One election can have many voting scopes
- **Election → Parties**: One election can have many parties
- **Election → Positions**: One election can have many positions
- **Election → Candidates**: One election can have many candidates
- **Election → Voters**: One election can have many voters
- **Election → Votes**: One election can have many votes
- **Position → Candidates**: One position can have many candidates
- **Party → Candidates**: One party can have many candidates
- **VotingScope → Voters**: One voting scope can have many voters
- **VotingScope → Votes**: One voting scope can have many votes
- **User → Sessions**: One user can have many sessions
- **User → Tickets**: One user can have many tickets
- **User → Audits**: One user can have many audit entries

### Many-to-One Relationships
- **Users → Organization**: Many users can belong to one organization
- **Elections → Organization**: Many elections can belong to one organization
- **Candidates → Position**: Many candidates can run for one position
- **Candidates → Party**: Many candidates can belong to one party
- **Voters → VotingScope**: Many voters can belong to one voting scope
- **Votes → Candidate**: Many votes can be cast for one candidate
- **Votes → Voter**: Many votes can be cast by one voter

### Self-Referential Relationships
- **VotingScope → VotingScope**: Hierarchical voting scopes (parent-child)

### Unique Constraints
- **User.email**: Unique email per user
- **Voter.code**: Unique voter code globally
- **Voter.email + electionId**: Unique email per election
- **Party.name + electionId**: Unique party name per election
- **Position.title + electionId**: Unique position title per election
- **Vote.voterId + candidateId**: One vote per voter per candidate
- **Survey.voterId + electionId**: One survey per voter per election

## Indexing Strategy

### Performance Indexes
- **User.email**: For authentication lookups
- **User.role**: For role-based queries
- **User.organizationId**: For organization-based queries
- **Election.organizationId**: For organization-based queries
- **Election.status**: For status-based filtering
- **Voter.code**: For voter code lookups
- **Vote.electionId**: For election result queries
- **Audit.createdAt**: For chronological queries

### Composite Indexes
- **Election.startDate + endDate**: For date range queries
- **Vote.electionId + votingScopeId**: For scope-based results
- **Audit.entityType + entityId**: For entity-specific audits

